title: Unemployment rate in Malawi 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Unemployment rate. In total the number of data points it has is 21.
In general Unemployment rate has fallen over the Year.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2005 and 2006.
Maximum Unemployment rate, about 8.43 was reported at Year 1999
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 5.38 was reported at Year 2019
